title: Woman, 90, dies in house fire
title_page: Oxford: Woman, 90, dies in house fire - BBC News
maintext:
A 90-year-old woman has died after a fire in Oxford.
Thames Valley Police said she died in Stubbs Avenue in Headington at about 05:20 GMT on Wednesday.
The death is being treated as unexplained but not suspicious and a file is being prepared for the coroner, police said.
The woman's next of kin have been informed and are being supported by officers.
